karlnet.name: karlnet

revisions.description: Several minor updates; also added ClientInfo and SEC MIB sections.
Updated CONTACT-INFO. Added the kbSEC and kbClientInfo sections.
Changed kbWirelessStationSNR type from Gauge32 to INTEGER
Added description text on kbControlTemperature to clarify that the temperature given is in half-degree increments centigrade. That is, kbControlTemperature = 66 implies 33 degrees Celsius.

karlnet.description: The MIB module for KarlNet entities. iso(1).org(3).dod(6).internet(1).mgmt(4).enterprises(1).karlnet(762)

kbControlReboot.name: kbControlReboot
kbControlReboot.description: Set this OID value to 1 to reboot the KarlBridge.

kbControlTestSNMPWrite.name: kbControlTestSNMPWrite
kbControlTestSNMPWrite.description: This OID is provided to test whether your SNMP software can successfully set an OID on the KarlBridge by setting its value to 1.

kbControlShutdown.name: kbControlShutdown
kbControlShutdown.description: Set this OID to 1 to shutdown the KarlBridge.

kbControlTemperature.name: kbControlTemperature
kbControlTemperature.description: For KarlBridges equipped with a Dallas temperature chip, returns the temperature of the Dallas chip in 1/2 degree centigrade increments (+/- 0.5 degrees C). To determine the correct temperature in Centigrade, divide by 2. To determine the correct temperature in Fahrenheit, divide by 2, then multiply by 9/5 and add 32. KarlBridges that are not equipped with the Dallas chip return a 'noSuchName' error.

kbWirelessStationNumber.name: kbWirelessStationNumber
kbWirelessStationNumber.description: The number of registered stations (i.e. valid entries) in the kbWirelessStationTable.

kbWirelessStationTable.name: kbWirelessStationTable
kbWirelessStationTable.description: List of wireless connections and their attributes. Each entry in the table corresponds to a particular wireless station (usually a satellite) that is attached to a particular wireless interface.

kbWirelessStationEntry.name: kbWirelessStationEntry
kbWirelessStationEntry.description: An entry in the kbWirelessStationTable. Each entry corresponds to a particular wireless station connected to one of the KarlBridge's interfaces. The entries are indexed by kbWirelessStationIndex and also can be generally considered unique based upon the kbWirelessStationMACAddress field.

kbWirelessStationIndex.name: kbWirelessStationIndex
kbWirelessStationIndex.description: The index of this entry in the kbWirelessStationTable. Each entry in the table has a unique kbWirelessStationIndex.

kbWirelessStationInterfaceNumber.name: kbWirelessStationInterfaceNumber
kbWirelessStationInterfaceNumber.description: The interface number of the wireless network interface that this entry is attached to. When a KarlBridge contains multiple wireless network interfaces, different entries may contain different values for this field. Interface numbering includes non-wireless interfaces, with the first network interface being number 1.

kbWirelessStationName.name: kbWirelessStationName
kbWirelessStationName.description: The name of the remote wireless station as reported to the KarlBridge.

kbWirelessStationExclHellos.name: kbWirelessStationExclHellos
kbWirelessStationExclHellos.description: The number of Hello packets from the KarlBridge that were received by the remote station with Excellent signal quality.

kbWirelessStationGoodHellos.name: kbWirelessStationGoodHellos
kbWirelessStationGoodHellos.description: The number of Hello packets from the KarlBridge that were received by the remote station with Good signal quality.

kbWirelessStationLowHellos.name: kbWirelessStationLowHellos
kbWirelessStationLowHellos.description: The number of Hello packets from the KarlBridge that were received by the remote station with Low signal quality.

kbWirelessStationSignalLevel.name: kbWirelessStationSignalLevel
kbWirelessStationSignalLevel.description: The radio signal level in percentage.

kbWirelessStationNoiseLevel.name: kbWirelessStationNoiseLevel
kbWirelessStationNoiseLevel.description: The radio noise level in percentage.

kbWirelessStationSignalQuality.name: kbWirelessStationSignalQuality
kbWirelessStationSignalQuality.description: The relative signal quality of the radio transmissions.

kbWirelessStationPktTransmits.name: kbWirelessStationPktTransmits
kbWirelessStationPktTransmits.description: The number of Ethernet packets the remote station has transmitted through the wireless interface connected to the KarlBridge.

kbWirelessStationMACAddress.name: kbWirelessStationMACAddress
kbWirelessStationMACAddress.description: The Ethernet (MAC) address of the remote station's wireless interface that is connected to the KarlBridge.

kbWirelessStationTransmits.name: kbWirelessStationTransmits
kbWirelessStationTransmits.description: The total number of wireless transmissions the KarlBridge has made to the remote station through this interface. This number does not necessarily correspond to the number of Ethernet packets transmitted through this interface (see kbWirelessStationPktTransmits).

kbWirelessStationBadTransmits.name: kbWirelessStationBadTransmits
kbWirelessStationBadTransmits.description: The total number of failed wireless transmissions the KarlBridge has made to the remote station through this interface. If a wireless transmission is not received after 10 attempts, this counter is incremented.

kbWirelessStationReTransmits.name: kbWirelessStationReTransmits
kbWirelessStationReTransmits.description: The total number of wireless re-transmissions the KarlBridge has attempted to the remote station through this interface.

kbWirelessStationIPAddress.name: kbWirelessStationIPAddress
kbWirelessStationIPAddress.description: The IP address of the remote station, if any.

kbWirelessStationType.name: kbWirelessStationType
kbWirelessStationType.description: The remote station's mode of operation on this radio interface. Possible values are: compatibility-Mode(1) -- IEEE 802.11 mode or legacy Wireless(-I) mode tc-Peer-to-Peer(2) -- TurboCell Peer-to-Peer Station (no base stations, no polling) tc-Base-Station(3) -- TurboCell Base Station tc-Satellite-Station(4) -- TurboCell Satellite Station tc-Polling-Base-Station(5) -- TurboCell Polling Base Station tc-PtP-Controller(6) -- TurboCell Point-to-Point Controller (Single-User Base Station)

kbWirelessStationSNR.name: kbWirelessStationSNR
kbWirelessStationSNR.description: The relative Signal-to-Noise Ratio of the wireless connection between the remote station and the KarlBridge.

kbWirelessStationState.name: kbWirelessStationState
kbWirelessStationState.description: The remote station's wireless connection status. The remote station is said to be offline when it appears to cease wireless communication, either because it no longer acknowledges poll packets or no longer sends poll packets

kbWirelessPoll.name: kbWirelessPoll
kbWirelessPoll.description: The number of times the KarlBridge has polled the remote station.

kbWirelessPollData.name: kbWirelessPollData
kbWirelessPollData.description: The number of times the KarlBridge has polled the remote station that the remote station has responded with data, after which the remote station's transmit queue is empty.

kbWirelessPollNoData.name: kbWirelessPollNoData
kbWirelessPollNoData.description: The number of times the KarlBridge has polled the remote station that the remote station has not responded with data.

kbWirelessPollMoreData.name: kbWirelessPollMoreData
kbWirelessPollMoreData.description: The number of times the KarlBridge has polled the remote station that the remote station has had more data in its transmit queue than it could transmit in a single poll response.

kbWirelessPollTimeouts.name: kbWirelessPollTimeouts
kbWirelessPollTimeouts.description: The number of times the KarlBridge has polled the remote station and the remote station has not responded before the timeout period expired.

kbWirelessPollOfflines.name: kbWirelessPollOfflines
kbWirelessPollOfflines.description: The number of times the remote station has gone offline. The value is relevant only when the KarlBridge is in one of the Base Station modes (polling or non-polling).

kbWirelessTestTime.name: kbWirelessTestTime
kbWirelessTestTime.description: The number of seconds remaining in the wireless link test. This value is read-writable, and is decremented by the device every second until it reaches 0, at which point the test is finished. To stop the test, set this value to 0.

kbWirelessTestInterval.name: kbWirelessTestInterval
kbWirelessTestInterval.description: The duration (in hundredths of seconds) of the radio link test performed between the KarlBridge and the remote station.

kbWirelessTestPacketSize.name: kbWirelessTestPacketSize
kbWirelessTestPacketSize.description: The size of the radio link test packets sent between the KarlBridge and the remote station.

kbWirelessTestOurTx.name: kbWirelessTestOurTx
kbWirelessTestOurTx.description: The radio transmit rate of the KarlBridge's radio when performing the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestOurRx.name: kbWirelessTestOurRx
kbWirelessTestOurRx.description: The radio receive rate used by the KarlBridge when performing the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisTx.name: kbWirelessTestHisTx
kbWirelessTestHisTx.description: The radio transmit rate of the remote station's radio when performing the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisRx.name: kbWirelessTestHisRx
kbWirelessTestHisRx.description: The radio receive rate used by the remote station when performing the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestOurCurSignalLevel.name: kbWirelessTestOurCurSignalLevel
kbWirelessTestOurCurSignalLevel.description: The current local signal level for the radio link test as recorded by the KarlBridge.

kbWirelessTestOurCurNoiseLevel.name: kbWirelessTestOurCurNoiseLevel
kbWirelessTestOurCurNoiseLevel.description: The current local noise level for the radio link test as recorded by the KarlBridge.

kbWirelessTestOurCurSignalQuality.name: kbWirelessTestOurCurSignalQuality
kbWirelessTestOurCurSignalQuality.description: The current relative signal quality for the radio link test as recorded by the KarlBridge.

kbWirelessTestOurCurSNR.name: kbWirelessTestOurCurSNR
kbWirelessTestOurCurSNR.description: The current local Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR) for the radio link test as recorded by the KarlBridge.

kbWirelessTestOurMinSignalLevel.name: kbWirelessTestOurMinSignalLevel
kbWirelessTestOurMinSignalLevel.description: The minimum local signal level recorded by the KarlBridge during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestOurMinNoiseLevel.name: kbWirelessTestOurMinNoiseLevel
kbWirelessTestOurMinNoiseLevel.description: The minimum local noise level recorded by the KarlBridge during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestOurMinSignalQuality.name: kbWirelessTestOurMinSignalQuality
kbWirelessTestOurMinSignalQuality.description: The minimum local signal quality recorded by the KarlBridge during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestOurMinSNR.name: kbWirelessTestOurMinSNR
kbWirelessTestOurMinSNR.description: The minimum local Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR) recorded by the KarlBridge during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestOurMaxSignalLevel.name: kbWirelessTestOurMaxSignalLevel
kbWirelessTestOurMaxSignalLevel.description: The maximum local signal level recorded by the KarlBridge during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestOurMaxNoiseLevel.name: kbWirelessTestOurMaxNoiseLevel
kbWirelessTestOurMaxNoiseLevel.description: The maximum local noise level recorded by the KarlBridge during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestOurMaxSignalQuality.name: kbWirelessTestOurMaxSignalQuality
kbWirelessTestOurMaxSignalQuality.description: The maximum local signal quality recorded by the KarlBridge during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestOurMaxSNR.name: kbWirelessTestOurMaxSNR
kbWirelessTestOurMaxSNR.description: The maximum local Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR) recorded by the KarlBridge during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisCurSignalLevel.name: kbWirelessTestHisCurSignalLevel
kbWirelessTestHisCurSignalLevel.description: The current signal level at the remote station for the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisCurNoiseLevel.name: kbWirelessTestHisCurNoiseLevel
kbWirelessTestHisCurNoiseLevel.description: The current noise level at the remote station for the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisCurSignalQuality.name: kbWirelessTestHisCurSignalQuality
kbWirelessTestHisCurSignalQuality.description: The current signal quality at the remote station for the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisCurSNR.name: kbWirelessTestHisCurSNR
kbWirelessTestHisCurSNR.description: The current Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR) at the remote station for the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisMinSignalLevel.name: kbWirelessTestHisMinSignalLevel
kbWirelessTestHisMinSignalLevel.description: The minimum signal level recorded at the remote station during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisMinNoiseLevel.name: kbWirelessTestHisMinNoiseLevel
kbWirelessTestHisMinNoiseLevel.description: The minimum noise level recorded at the remote station during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisMinSignalQuality.name: kbWirelessTestHisMinSignalQuality
kbWirelessTestHisMinSignalQuality.description: The minimum signal quality recorded at the remote station during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisMinSNR.name: kbWirelessTestHisMinSNR
kbWirelessTestHisMinSNR.description: The minimum signal level recorded at the remote station during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisMaxSignalLevel.name: kbWirelessTestHisMaxSignalLevel
kbWirelessTestHisMaxSignalLevel.description: The maximum signal level recorded at the remote station during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisMaxNoiseLevel.name: kbWirelessTestHisMaxNoiseLevel
kbWirelessTestHisMaxNoiseLevel.description: The maximum remote noise level recorded at the remote station during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisMaxSignalQuality.name: kbWirelessTestHisMaxSignalQuality
kbWirelessTestHisMaxSignalQuality.description: The maximum signal quality recorded at the remote station during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestHisMaxSNR.name: kbWirelessTestHisMaxSNR
kbWirelessTestHisMaxSNR.description: The maximum Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR) recorded at the remote station during the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestLinkUp.name: kbWirelessTestLinkUp
kbWirelessTestLinkUp.description: The status of the radio link test. Possible values are: down(0) -- the radio link test IS NOT currently running up(1) -- the radio link test IS currently running

kbWirelessTestLostLink.name: kbWirelessTestLostLink
kbWirelessTestLostLink.description: The number of time this link was lost while performing the radio link test.

kbWirelessTestLostTestPkts.name: kbWirelessTestLostTestPkts
kbWirelessTestLostTestPkts.description: The total number of radio link test packets that were lost during the test interval.

kbWirelessStationRadioType.name: kbWirelessStationRadioType
kbWirelessStationRadioType.description: The type of radio the remote station is using on this interface. Possible values include: waveLAN-I(0) -- legacy Lucent Wireless-I radio (900 MHz) clarion-M10(1) -- Clarion M10 radio waveLAN-IEEE(2) -- Lucent ORiNOCO (WaveLAN) IEEE 802.11 radio (2.4 GHz) microwave(3) -- some type of microwave radio radioLAN(4) -- some type of RadioLAN radio

kbWirelessRecordType.name: kbWirelessRecordType
kbWirelessRecordType.description: The type of this record entry. Possible values include: linktest(1) -- This record contains ONLY LinkTest results turboCell(2) -- This record contains ONLY a TurboCell station entry combination(3) -- This record contains BOTH LinkTest results AND a TurboCell station entry

kbWirelessStationPktReceives.name: kbWirelessStationPktReceives
kbWirelessStationPktReceives.description: The number of packets the KarlBridge has received on this link.

kbWirelessStationReceives.name: kbWirelessStationReceives
kbWirelessStationReceives.description: The number of wireless transmissions the KarlBridge has received on this link.

kbWirelessStationBytesReceives.name: kbWirelessStationBytesReceives
kbWirelessStationBytesReceives.description: The number of bytes received by the KarlBridge on this link, including wireless packet headers.

kbWirelessStationBytesTransmits.name: kbWirelessStationBytesTransmits
kbWirelessStationBytesTransmits.description: The number of bytes transmitted by the KarlBridge on this link, including wireless packet headers.

kbWirelessStationFragmentDiscards.name: kbWirelessStationFragmentDiscards
kbWirelessStationFragmentDiscards.description: The number of times on this connection that the KarlBridge has discarded a fragment. A fragment is discarded because not all fragments needed to reconstruct a packet are present or we need room for a more recent fragment.

kbWirelessStationFragmentMissings.name: kbWirelessStationFragmentMissings
kbWirelessStationFragmentMissings.description: The number of times on this connection that the KarlBridge has detected that a fragment needed to recontruct a packet is missing.

kbWirelessStationFragmentLostFrames.name: kbWirelessStationFragmentLostFrames
kbWirelessStationFragmentLostFrames.description: The number of times on this connection that the KarlBridge detected that a frame containing fragments needed to reconstruct a packet is lost.

kbWirelessStationFragmentErrors.name: kbWirelessStationFragmentErrors
kbWirelessStationFragmentErrors.description: The number of times on this connection the KarlBridge has encountered an error while reconstructing a packet from fragments.

kbSECClientTable.name: kbSECClientTable
kbSECClientTable.description: A table that contains information about Super Ethernet Converter (SEC) clients and the SEC station through which they are connected.

kbSECClientEntry.name: kbSECClientEntry
kbSECClientEntry.description: An entry in the kbSECClientTable. Each entry contains the client's MAC address (which is the table index) and the MAC address of the SEC through which the client is connected.

kbSECClientAddress.name: kbSECClientAddress
kbSECClientAddress.description: The unicast MAC address of the client station that is connecting through the SEC unit denoted by kbSECStationAddress.

kbSECStationAddress.name: kbSECStationAddress
kbSECStationAddress.description: The unicast MAC address of the SEC station through which the client is connected.

kbClientInfoByNumberTable.name: kbClientInfoByNumberTable
kbClientInfoByNumberTable.description: A table that contains information about (wireless) clients that pass traffic through this KarlBridge, indexed by a virtual port number that is unique only within this table.

kbClientInfoByNumberEntry.name: kbClientInfoByNumberEntry
kbClientInfoByNumberEntry.description: An entry in the kbClientInfoByNumberTable. Each entry contains information for a particular client station indexed by the client's virtual port number.

kbCIbyNumberVirtualPort.name: kbCIbyNumberVirtualPort
kbCIbyNumberVirtualPort.description: The virtual port number to which the client is connected. Used as the index for this table.

kbCIbyNumberMACAddress.name: kbCIbyNumberMACAddress
kbCIbyNumberMACAddress.description: The client's unique unicast MAC Address. This value can be used as the index in the kbClientInfoByMacTable.

kbCIByNumberInterfaceNum.name: kbCIByNumberInterfaceNum
kbCIByNumberInterfaceNum.description: The KarlBridge interface to which the client is connected.

kbCIbyNumberTotalBytes.name: kbCIbyNumberTotalBytes
kbCIbyNumberTotalBytes.description: The total number of bytes that have been passed through the KarlBridge for this client (clientTotalBytes = clientSentBytes + clientRecvBytes)

kbCIbyNumberTotalPackets.name: kbCIbyNumberTotalPackets
kbCIbyNumberTotalPackets.description: The total number of packets that have been passed through the KarlBridge for this client (clientTotalPackets = clientSentPackets + clientRecvPackets)

kbCIbyNumberSNRAverage.name: kbCIbyNumberSNRAverage
kbCIbyNumberSNRAverage.description: The running average of the Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR) for this client, if the client is connected directly to the KarlBridge on a wireless interface. 0 otherwise.

kbCIbyNumberTimeLastRecv.name: kbCIbyNumberTimeLastRecv
kbCIbyNumberTimeLastRecv.description: The number of time ticks (in 1/100ths of a second) since a packet was last received from this client.

kbClientInfoByMacTable.name: kbClientInfoByMacTable
kbClientInfoByMacTable.description: A table that contains information about (wireless) clients that pass traffic through this KarlBridge, indexed by client MAC Address.

kbClientInfoByMacEntry.name: kbClientInfoByMacEntry
kbClientInfoByMacEntry.description: An entry in the kbClientInfoByMacTable. Each entry contains information for a particular client station indexed by the client's unique MAC Address.

kbCIbyMacMACAddress.name: kbCIbyMacMACAddress
kbCIbyMacMACAddress.description: The client's unique unicast MAC Address. Used as the index for this table.

kbCIbyMacVirtualPort.name: kbCIbyMacVirtualPort
kbCIbyMacVirtualPort.description: The virtual port number to which the client is connected. This value can be used as the index in the kbClientInfoByNumberTable.

kbCIbyMacInterfaceNum.name: kbCIbyMacInterfaceNum
kbCIbyMacInterfaceNum.description: The KarlBridge interface to which the client is connected.

kbCIbyMacTotalBytes.name: kbCIbyMacTotalBytes
kbCIbyMacTotalBytes.description: The total number of bytes that have been passed through the KarlBridge for this client (clientTotalBytes = clientSentBytes + clientRecvBytes)

kbCIbyMacTotalPackets.name: kbCIbyMacTotalPackets
kbCIbyMacTotalPackets.description: The total number of packets that have been passed through the KarlBridge for this client (clientTotalPackets = clientSentPackets + clientRecvPackets)

kbCIbyMacSNRAverage.name: kbCIbyMacSNRAverage
kbCIbyMacSNRAverage.description: The running average of the Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR) for this client, if the client is connected directly to the KarlBridge on a wireless interface. 0 otherwise.

kbCIbyMacTimeLastRecv.name: kbCIbyMacTimeLastRecv
kbCIbyMacTimeLastRecv.description: The number of time ticks (in 1/100ths of a second) since a packet was last received from this client.
